---
import SiteLayout from '../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import PrinterTable from '../../components/PrinterTable.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Best No-Subscription Printers"
  description="A practical guide to printers that do not require mandatory ink subscriptions, with notes on refillable tanks, toner, Linux support, and lock-in risk."
>
  <div class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Buyer guide</p>
    <h1>Best no-subscription printers to research first.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A no-subscription printer should still work normally if you never join an ink plan. This first guide prioritizes ownership clarity over flashy app features.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--amber);">Starter picks</p>
          <h2>Models that fit the no-lock-in thesis</h2>
        </div>
        <p>These are research candidates for the local preview. Full production pages should add current price checks, exact cartridge numbers, and availability notes.</p>
      </div>
      <PrinterTable category="no-subscription" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="article">
    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>What “no subscription” should mean</h2>
      <p>
        It should mean the printer is usable without a paid ink plan, cloud account dependency, or surprise feature loss when you cancel. Optional supply programs are less risky than printers whose value proposition depends on staying subscribed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="article-section">
      <h2>Buying checklist</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Can it print over USB, local network, AirPrint, or CUPS without a vendor cloud account?</li>
        <li>Are standard cartridges, toner, or refill bottles available from more than one retailer?</li>
        <li>Do firmware updates affect third-party supplies or older cartridges?</li>
        <li>Does the printer keep working if an optional ink subscription is canceled?</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
